lenders.name: Fibronectin
lenders.occupational_info:
Fibronectin is an extracellular matrix protein that is found abundantly in blood and connective tissues. These matrices are associated with the epithelial to mesenchymal transition of metasltatic cells, including tumor cells with stem cell-like properties. Fibronectin performs essential functions in collagen fibrillogenesis, as either a general cell adhesion molecule or a modulator in binding between cell surfaces and the extracellular matrix. Fibronectin matrix assembly is essential for normal vertebrate development and apparently contributes to the generation of tumor metastases by supporting the establishment and persistence of pre-metastatic niches. Fibronectin is secreted as a disulfide-like dimer of 230-270kDa, comprised of three types of repeating modules that mediate interactions with extracellular matrix components and cells via integrins and other fibronectin receptors. Thus, fibronectin can be used for coating culture coverslips to promote cell adhesion and proliferation.
                At VitroCam we coat German glass coverslips using the latest coating technology.  The coverslips are coated using third 
generation digitized techniques, so you can be assured of consistent results.Our coverslips are coated in a range of six different surfaces and come in sizes from 12mm to 25mm.  We also offer different thicknesses.For more information visit our website:- www.vitrocam.com

lenders.name: Ben Davidson
lenders.occupational_info:
Rodic Davidson Architects, a London Practice that has developed a reputation for commercial ingenuity, vision and the ability to create crisp, elegant and finely-designed architecture Ben Davidson RIBA created Rodic Davidson Architects in August 2006, and the new practice quickly found a home in London's Mayfair. Rodic Davidson Architects work across several different types of projects. Their expertise is not limited to conventional architecture. Not only that, they are experienced in interior design, sustainability and development. The company is a RIBA Chartered Practice and undertakes commissions for new-build houses, flats and renovation/remodeling throughout London. Listed buildings can sometimes make life challenging, but this is not an issue for Rodic Davidson Architects. They do not just have the skills and knowhow to work with historic properties; they also have the ability to obtain the consents needed to get the job done. Ben Davidson, the eponymous founder of Rodic Davidson Architects, is widely regarded as a master of negotiation. He has closed planning and development deals with a wide array of influential parties, including highly regarded London Estates. Ben has worked extensively with Listed Structures; particularly within Kensington and Chelsea, Westminster, Camden and Hammersmith and Fulham. Ben considers that good architecture and powerful design in the build atmosphere can result in increased sales for companies. When he is not engaged with client business, Ben occasionally lectures at the University of the Arts, London. Ben founded bdAr Architects and Designers (later to become Rodic Davidson Architects) Sinisa Rodic joined bdAr in 2007 as Head of Design and has since been responsible for a variety of projects spanning from esteemed central London refurbishments to global master planning proposals. No matter how tight a short is, Sinisa somehow succeeds to extract an elegant solution every time. He puts this down to being inspired by restriction; a tough brief drives him to make some thing truly innovative. The architecture he has done while in the past features a range of influences and designs. It is because he creates function that's specifically tailored to the task at hand, instead of wheeling out his personal preferences at every chance. Sinisa works across many different projects, and this has been a great benefit to the culture at Rodic Davidson Architects. By refusing to specialize in just one area, the practice has increased their levels of innovation and design quality across all areas. The output of Rodic Davidson Architects is a reflection of their practical, sensible approach to contemporary design. We believe that a comprehensive understanding of client needs leads to the best quality design solutions. We have a list of happy customers across the world of property development, and we've also successfully finished projects for owner-occupiers. Architecturally we are a practice, but that is not the start and ending of the story. Our project management abilities also help us to work with our customers and produce the very best solutions, on budget. We have incredible contacts across all areas of architecture and construction that we can leverage on your project. We pride ourselves on producing advanced architectural solutions on all types of building, for any kind of client. From enormous office buildings for developers or small residences for individuals, we can get incredible results within a strict budget. We are glad to deal with a range of projects, including new-builds and renovation/remodeling. The bulk of our jobs are in the London boroughs of Kensington and Chelsea, Westminster, Hammersmith and Fulham and Camden. We consistently work with listed buildings and so are specialists in obtaining the necessary listed building consents. We're one of London's most well connected architectural practices, and our contact list includes some of the capital's most esteemed building professionals.
